                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian Pauncefote</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian"
                            type="received-date" when="1894-08-24">undated</date>].</dateline>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Memorandum. Handed to the Secretary of State by the
                        British ambassador, August 24, 1894.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>The Earl of Kimberley assumes that sections 182½ and 89 will on coming into force
                    entirely cancel the agreements made with the West Indies under the McKinley act,
                    and that they would not be continued by the passage of an act making sugar
                    duty-free indiscriminately.</p>
            </div>
